# UX system — reuse before you create

Before implementing UI, **search and reuse** pieces in `src/shared/components/`:

| Need | Start with |
|------|------------|
| Screen layout | `ScreenShell`, `ScreenBody`, `SectionCard` |
| Text and titles | `TextParagraph`, `TextHeading`, `TextLabel`, `TextLegal` |
| Actions and forms | `Button`, `InputField`, `InputNumeric`, `SearchField` |
| Empty / error / loading | `ContentEmptyState`, `ReloadState`, `SkeletonBone` |
| Headers and tabs | `HeaderScreen`, `HeaderSection`, `TabHeader`, `TabPill` |
| Feedback | `InfoHint`, `Badge`, `StatusIcon`, toasts via overlay |

## Required workflow

1. Check `@/shared/components/ui/index.ts` and the component family folder (`headers/`, `layout/`, `inputs/`, …).
2. If an equivalent exists, **use it** (extend props or add a `variant` for minor gaps).
3. Create a new component only when nothing reusable fits; place it per [ADR-003](../../docs/architecture/adr-003-component-naming.md):
   - generic → `shared/components/<family>/`
   - feature-specific → `features/<feature>/components/`

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — ad hoc empty state
<View className="rounded-card bg-surface p-md">
  <Text>No funds found</Text>
</View>

// ✅ GOOD — existing design system
<ContentEmptyState title="No funds found" description="Try another filter." />
```

Do not duplicate styles for tokenized atoms. Use `cn()` and semantic tokens (`bg-surface`, `rounded-card`, `text-text-secondary`).
